FBIS4-5217 "dreas068_d_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 South Korea President Kim Talks With Japan's Hosokawa President Kim Talks With Japan's Hosokawa SK0804112294 Seoul YONHAP in English 1115 GMT 8 Apr 94 SK0804112294 Seoul YONHAP English BFN [Text] Seoul, April 8 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam had a telephone conversation with outgoing Japanese Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa Friday afternoon, in which Kim consoled the resigning premier. The telephone talks lasted about 15 minutes beginning 6 P.M. It was called by Hosokawa. The Japanese prime minister explained to President Kim about the background that led him to decide to resign as premier and thanked the president for the cooperation Kim showed to him. President Kim said there would be no change in his friendship with and trust in Prime Minister Hosokawa, which he said had been cemented through mutual visits and summit talks.
